<img src="https://images.code.org/54ec59024257ed9adbbf43ddb9383dd4-Screenshot 2025-05-20 at 2.35.37 PM.png" alt="phone icon" style="border-radius:10px; float: left; height: 120px; width: 120px; margin: 20px 20px 0px 10px; ">

## Scenario B:
#### A website requires users to verify their identity using two-factor authentication before logging in.

<details style="background-color: #ececec; padding: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 145px; width: 45%; border: 1px solid transparent; border-radius: 5px;">
    <summary style="font-size: 14pt; font-weight: bold;"><b>🔎</b>  Answer</summary>
<div style="margin-top: 10px; margin-left: 10px; margin-right: 10px; padding-bottom:0px;">
       	<p style= "font-size: 14pt">
        <b>Cybersecurity-</b> <i>Two-factor authentication (2FA) is a security measure that adds an extra layer of protection to user accounts by requiring a second form of verification, such as a code sent to a phone or email.</i>
        </p>
   </div>
</details>

<div style="clear:both;"></div>
<br>

<img src="https://images.code.org/382eb625af5f1936acceaf15fa44bb1a-Screenshot 2025-05-20 at 2.35.42 PM.png" alt="cook book icon" style="border-radius:10px; float: left; height: 120px; width: 120px; margin: 20px 20px 0px 10px; ">

## Scenario C:
#### A chef stores recipes in a physical cookbook to keep track of ingredients.

<details style="background-color: #ececec; padding: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 145px; width: 45%; border: 1px solid transparent; border-radius: 5px;">
    <summary style="font-size: 14pt; font-weight: bold;"><b>🔎</b>  Answer</summary>
<div style="margin-top: 10px; margin-left: 10px; margin-right: 10px; padding-bottom:0px;">
       	<p style= "font-size: 14pt">
        <b>Not Cybersecurity-</b> <i>This is a physical record-keeping practice and does not involve digital security or protecting information from cyber threats.</i>
        </p>
   </div>
</details>

<div style="clear:both;"></div>
<br>

<img src="https://images.code.org/56ee76ae717e0695093a79d9d952ee6a-Screenshot 2025-05-20 at 2.35.47 PM.png" alt="computer icon" style="border-radius:10px; float: left; height: 120px; width: 120px; margin: 20px 20px 0px 10px; ">

## Scenario D:
#### A bank encrypts online transactions to protect customers from fraud and cyberattacks.

<details style="background-color: #ececec; padding: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 145px; width: 45%; border: 1px solid transparent; border-radius: 5px;">
    <summary style="font-size: 14pt; font-weight: bold;"><b>🔎</b>  Answer</summary>
<div style="margin-top: 10px; margin-left: 10px; margin-right: 10px; padding-bottom:0px;">
       	<p style= "font-size: 14pt">
        <b>Cybersecurity-</b> <i>Encryption is a cybersecurity technique that secures sensitive information by converting it into unreadable data, ensuring that only authorized users can access it.</i>
        </p>
   </div>
</details>

<div style="clear:both;"></div>
<br>

<img src="https://images.code.org/b8f7f144f3137f9c7115edfcbbb75b33-Screenshot 2025-05-20 at 2.35.55 PM.png" alt="computer icon" style="border-radius:10px; float: left; height: 120px; width: 120px; margin: 20px 20px 0px 10px; ">

## Scenario E:
#### A school district installs content filtering software to prevent students from accessing harmful websites.

<details style="background-color: #ececec; padding: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 145px; width: 45%; border: 1px solid transparent; border-radius: 5px;">
    <summary style="font-size: 14pt; font-weight: bold;"><b>🔎</b>  Answer</summary>
<div style="margin-top: 10px; margin-left: 10px; margin-right: 10px; padding-bottom:0px;">
       	<p style= "font-size: 14pt">
        <b>Cybersecurity-</b> <i>Content filtering is a cybersecurity measure used to block or restrict access to malicious or inappropriate websites, protecting students from online threats.</i>
        </p>
   </div>
</details>

<div style="clear:both;"></div>
<br>

<div style="background-color: #a6e3e8; border-radius: 40px; color: #000000; width: 95%; padding: 1px 20px 1px 20px;">

